#Approach:

**Hinglish quick revision:**

Tumhara approach sahi hai:

* recursively right side ko flatten karo
* current list ko flattened right list ke saath merge karo
* final answer `child` pointer se return karo

Bas ek important issue hai:
**old `next` pointers null nahi kar rahe ho**

Flattened list sirf `child` pointer se honi chahiye, isliye merge ke time:
`temp.next = null`
karna better hai.

**Approach yaad rakhne ke liye:**

* `head.next` ko pehle flatten karo
* current vertical list + flattened right list ko merge karo
* merge exactly sorted linked list merge jaisa hai, bas `next` ki jagah `child` use hoga

**Time Complexity:** O(N * k) worst case
**Space Complexity:** O(k) recursion stack
where `k` = number of top-level lists


#Code:

/*Definition for singly Linked List
class ListNode {
    int val;
    ListNode next;
    ListNode child;

    ListNode() {
        val = 0;
        next = null;
        child = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1) {
        val = data1;
        next = null;
        child = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1, ListNode next1, ListNode next2) {
        val = data1;
        next = next1;
        child = next2;
    }
}
*/
class Solution {

    private ListNode merge(ListNode headA, ListNode headB){
        ListNode t1 = headA;
        ListNode t2 = headB;
        ListNode dummyNode = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode temp = dummyNode;
        while(t1 != null && t2 != null){
            if(t1.val < t2.val){
                temp.child = t1;
                temp = temp.child;
                t1 = t1.child;
            }
            else if(t1.val > t2.val){
                temp.child = t2;
                temp = temp.child;
                t2 = t2.child;
            }
            else{
                //if both are equal values
                temp.child = t1;
                temp = temp.child;
                t1 = t1.child;
            }
            temp.next = null;
        }
        //if t2 is exhausted
        while(t1 != null){
            temp.child = t1;
            temp = temp.child;
            t1 = t1.child;
            temp.next = null;
        }
        //if t1 is exhausted
        while(t2 != null){
            temp.child = t2;
            temp = temp.child;
            t2 = t2.child;
            temp.next = null;
        }

        return dummyNode.child;
    }

    private ListNode function(ListNode head){
        if(head == null || head.next == null){
            return head;
        }
        ListNode mergedHead = function(head.next);
        return merge(head, mergedHead);
    }

    public ListNode flattenLinkedList(ListNode head) {

        ListNode newHead = function(head);
        return newHead;
    }
}
